        <h2 id="general" class="text-font2">Basic Education Cluster</h2>
        <div class="content" id="content">
            <br>
            <p class="text-font2"><b>Andrew L Gotianun Sr Center for Integrated Technologies</b></p>
            <p class="text-font3">The Andrew L Gotianun Sr Center for Integrated Technologies (ALGCIT) Senior High School is an endowment from the Andrew L Gotianun Foundation for a two-year residential Tech-Voc Senior High School to competent yet financially disadvantaged youth. 
            <p class="text-font3">The program features (1) quality instruction and learning environment, (2) intensive Jesuit formation, and (3) an extended academic, community, and on-the-job experience. Full tuition, matriculation, medical tests, and other school fees are all covered by this scholarship.</p>
            <br>
            <p class="text-font2"><b>Senior High School (Academic Track)</b></p>
            <p class="text-font3">Senior High School is the additional two years (Grades 11 and 12) in the K to 12 Program. The two years will be added after the four-year Junior High School (Grades 7-10) program to provide sufficient time for mastery of concepts and skills, develop lifelong learners, and prepare graduates for tertiary education, middle level skills development, employment and entrepreneurship.</p>
            <br>
            <p class="text-font2"><b>Junior High</b></p>
            <p class="text-font3">Xavier University High School, as an integral part of the Xavier University educational apostolate, is Jesuit in origin, Catholic in its orientation, and Filipino in its concerns.</p>
            <p class="text-font3">Recognizing the unique historical role of Xavier University in the development and growth of Cagayan de Oro and Northern Mindanao,</p>
            <p class="text-font3"><b>Xavier University High School</b></p>
            <li>in a partnership of Jesuits, Lay Faculty & Staff, and parents, and</li>
            <li>in collaboration with other members of the Xavier University Community,</li>
            <li>employing a pedagogy which integrates Ignatian spirituality with the principles of the Jesuit Ratio Studiorum,</li>
            <br>
            <p class="text-font3">educates and forms leaders for the region who are characterized by internal discipline, analytical and ordered in their judgment, critical while being open to new ideas, entrepreneurial to the concerns of the human person and the larger community, animated by the pursuit of excellence and the spirit of service to others.</p>
            <p class="text-font2"><b>Grade School</b></p>
            <p class="text-font3">Xavier University Grade School is a vibrant community of young learners. Our pupils are at the heart of everything we do as we mold them to become “boys and girls for others” and form them as young leaders the Ateneo way. Xavier grade-schoolers are provided with excellent educational programs and conducive learning environment fit for their formative years.</p>
            <p class="text-font3">Guided by our vision to become “a leading ASEAN university forming leaders of character by 2033,” we challenge each young Atenean's mind, body and soul to achieve their highest potential. Co-curricular and extra-curricular activities boost more learning opportunities for their personal growth and collective development. With its modern facilities and multicultural setting, our school nurtures the talents and skills of the students as we prepare them for a world beyond borders.  </p>
            <p class="text-font2"><b>Preschool</b></p>
            <p class="text-font3">Xavier University Grade School is a vibrant community of young learners. Our pupils are at the heart of everything we do as we mold them to become “boys and girls for others” and form them as young leaders the Ateneo way. Xavier grade-schoolers are provided with excellent educational programs and conducive learning environment fit for their formative years.</p>
